F.  Web Graphic and Publication Designer (national, 18 person-months) 
6.  The consultant will help the team leader expand, improve, and operate the ARIC website 
by undertaking graphic design work. Under the supervision of OREI staff and the ARIC team 
leader, the consultant will: 

(i)  carry out design modifications to the existing website;  
(ii)  conceptualize and execute specified designs, including icons and thumbnails of 
new web pages and additional subsites;  
(iii)  conceptualize and implement the design of ARIC promotional materials; 
(iv)  lay out various OREI publications (e.g., AEM and the working paper series on 
regional economic integration), and ARIC documents (e.g., ARIC business plan, 
ARIC E-news); 
(v)  coordinate with other departments to ensure graphic design work of the website 
is consistent with design guidelines followed in ADB; and  
(vi)  carry out other tasks related to web graphical design as assigned by OREI staff. 

G.  Economic Analysts (national, total 81 person-months) 
7.  Five  consultants  will  help  the  team  leader  operate  the  ARIC  website,  develop  and 
update indicators, and prepare the AEM. Four consultants will each be engaged for 18 person-
months while one consultant will be engaged for 9 person-months. All economic analysts will 
have extensive experience in economic, social, and financial data processing and analysis; be 
familiar with regional cooperation and integration issues; have strong communication skills; and 
be proficient in standard computer applications. Under the supervision of OREI staff and the 
team leader, the consultants will: 

(i)  support the operation and development of the ARIC website; 
(ii)  maintain the following sections of the website: (a) money and finance, (b) trade 
integration indicators, (c) economic and financial (macro) indicators, and (d) other 
sections as may be required; 
(iii)  contribute to the improvement of the ARIC website; 
(iv)  assist in the preparation of AEM; 
(v)  provide other research and general administrative support as requested by the 
team leader or OREI staff.
